and peeked inside</i>

6
00:01:04,880 --> 00:01:07,240
<i>hoping you'd earn
enough money someday</i>

7
00:01:07,320 --> 00:01:10,000
<i>to afford the second-cheapest item.</i>

8
00:01:13,800 --> 00:01:15,000
<i>Surprise!</i>

9
00:01:16,880 --> 00:01:17,880
<i>You won't.</i>

10
00:01:23,720 --> 00:01:26,040
<i>But the last name was a curse too.</i>

11
00:01:30,480 --> 00:01:32,760
<i>It belonged to a Tuscan family.</i>

12
00:01:35,840 --> 00:01:40,400
<i>They didn't fight over land or crown.</i>

13
00:01:43,080 --> 00:01:44,200
- Good morning.
- <i>Ciao.</i>

14
00:01:44,280 --> 00:01:46,120
<i>They fought over their own skins.</i>

15
00:01:47,360 --> 00:01:48,480
<i>Signor</i> Gucci?

16
00:02:41,480 --> 00:02:43,800
Hey! Back to work.
Come on. Hey! Come on.

17
00:03:05,640 --> 00:03:06,640
Papa!

18
00:03:32,600 --> 00:03:34,400
Perfect. It's just like mine.

19
00:03:34,520 --> 00:03:36,560
Fernando Reggiani.

20
00:03:36,640 --> 00:03:37,640
(Italian)

21
00:03:38,680 --> 00:03:40,960
- Good girl.
- Hey, Fernando.

22
00:03:41,040 --> 00:03:43,200
- Hey.
- Your lunches are getting expensive.

23
00:03:43,920 --> 00:03:45,880
Because I have
expensive taste, huh?

24
00:03:48,760 --> 00:03:49,800
Don't tell Ma.

25
00:03:50,320 --> 00:03:51,320
She'll kill you.

26
00:03:52,520 --> 00:03:53,880
You don't tell your mother.

27
00:03:56,240 --> 00:03:57,240
Hello.

28
00:03:57,920 --> 00:04:00,200
Max. Darling.

29
00:04:01,480 --> 00:04:02,480
Tonight?

30
00:04:05,120 --> 00:04:06,160
I think I'm free.

31
00:04:24,560 --> 00:04:26,120
Do you like it? Yeah?

32
00:04:27,480 --> 00:04:28,760
This is fun!

33
00:04:37,760 --> 00:04:39,200
No, no.

34
00:04:55,440 --> 00:04:58,640
Tanqueray martini with a twist.

35
00:04:59,120 --> 00:05:00,400
I don't work here.

36
00:05:01,120 --> 00:05:02,880
Then why are you behind the bar?

37
00:05:03,800 --> 00:05:05,600
Is this part of your costume?

38
00:05:06,080 --> 00:05:07,080
I...

39
00:05:08,240 --> 00:05:10,440
I didn't know it was a costume party.

40
00:05:11,560 --> 00:05:12,720
The barten...

41
00:05:12,800 --> 00:05:14,360
The bartender...

42
00:05:15,960 --> 00:05:17,000
Yeah, I...

43
00:05:17,320 --> 00:05:18,400
I'll make you a drink.

44
00:05:19,680 --> 00:05:20,680
Thank you.

45
00:05:24,760 --> 00:05:26,160
Who invited you?

46
00:05:26,520 --> 00:05:27,560
Bianca.

47
00:05:27,960 --> 00:05:29,040
I don't know her.

48
00:05:30,200 --> 00:05:31,480
Bianca Sarzana.

49
00:05:34,120 --> 00:05:35,280
It's her party.

50
00:05:38,080 --> 00:05:40,800
Right. That Bianca.

51
00:05:42,840 --> 00:05:43,880
I'm Patrizia.

52
00:05:44,880 --> 00:05:45,880
Patrizia...

53
00:05:48,440 --> 00:05:49,560
Maurizio Gucci.

54
00:05:50,640 --> 00:05:52,320
It's a pleasure
to meet you, Patrizia.

55
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:55,280
It's a pleasure to meet you!

56
00:05:56,440 --> 00:05:57,480
You too.

57
00:05:58,720 --> 00:06:01,640
Patrizia, how come
I've never seen you before?

58
00:06:03,160 --> 00:06:04,800
You weren't looking hard enough.

59
00:06:05,480 --> 00:06:08,760
I would have noticed that Bianca
was friends with Elizabeth Taylor.

60
00:06:09,280 --> 00:06:10,480
I can assure you...

61
00:06:12,200 --> 00:06:13,400
I'm way more fun.

62
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:19,800
It's good.

63
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:24,800
Wanna dance?

64
00:06:25,720 --> 00:06:26,720
No.

65
00:06:30,240 --> 00:06:31,520
That's good. Come on.

66
00:07:08,280 --> 00:07:09,480
Is my dancing that bad?

67
00:07:09,560 --> 00:07:11,000
No... no.

68
00:07:13,920 --> 00:07:14,920
I have to go.

69
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:17,360
It's only midnight, Cinderella.

70
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:19,360
The night is young.

71
00:07:19,880 --> 00:07:21,880
I turn into a frog at midnight.

72
00:07:29,960 --> 00:07:31,560
It's nice to meet you, Patrizia.

73
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:41,320
It's a pumpkin.

74
00:07:41,680 --> 00:07:43,000
Not a frog.

75
00:08:19,720 --> 00:08:20,720
Hello.

76
00:08:21,280 --> 00:08:22,280
Hello.

77
00:08:24,640 --> 00:08:26,320
I'm sorry, have we met?

78
00:08:34,160 --> 00:08:35,160
Elizabeth Taylor.

79
00:08:36,840 --> 00:08:39,800
- Patrizia Reggiani.
- Yes, of course. Patrizia Reggiani.

80
00:08:43,120 --> 00:08:44,720
It's good to see you again.

81
00:08:45,120 --> 00:08:46,120
You too.

82
00:08:46,200 --> 00:08:47,360
Do you study here?

83
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:49,720
I'm considering it.

84
00:08:49,800 --> 00:08:53,000
The problem is I hate reading.
I get bored.

85
00:08:54,440 --> 00:08:55,440
Oh.

86
00:08:57,840 --> 00:08:58,840
What are those about?

87
00:08:59,360 --> 00:09:00,360
These are...

88
00:09:02,160 --> 00:09:08,560
Well, these are very exciting books
about the legislative process.

89
00:09:08,640 --> 00:09:10,200
I'm studying to be a lawyer.

90
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:12,720
You seem too nice to be a lawyer.

91
00:09:13,440 --> 00:09:15,880
Well, there are a few good ones.

92
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:17,360
The dead ones.

93
00:09:29,520 --> 00:09:32,120
What were the chances of
us seeing each other again?

94
00:09:32,560 --> 00:09:33,560
It's fate.

95
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:35,480
It was a really nice surprise.

96
00:09:44,600 --> 00:09:46,280
Aren't you going to ask me out?

97
00:09:48,720 --> 00:09:51,720
You... you wanna
go on a date with me?

98
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:56,000
Of course, I would...

99
00:09:56,080 --> 00:09:58,240
I want to see how this story goes.

100
00:10:01,800 --> 00:10:02,800
Yes...

101
00:10:08,800 --> 00:10:10,040
That's my number.

102
00:10:10,520 --> 00:10:14,080
I'm very busy,
but I'll make time for you...

103
00:10:15,640 --> 00:10:16,640
Maurizio.

104
00:10:21,600 --> 00:10:23,000
<i>- Ciao.
- Ciao.</i>

105
00:10:34,520 --> 00:10:35,520
It's for you.

106
00:10:47,240 --> 00:10:48,240
Hello?

107
00:10:53,200 --> 00:10:55,320
So do you think
you're gonna pass the bar soon?

108
00:10:55,920 --> 00:10:57,640
I think I have a...

109
00:10:57,720 --> 00:10:59,480
Would you like to go into this...

110
00:10:59,680 --> 00:11:01,176
- Oh, no. I can't eat there.
- This place?

111
00:11:01,200 --> 00:11:02,320
It's too expensive.

112
00:11:03,640 --> 00:11:04,640
Okay.

113
00:11:06,520 --> 00:11:07,600
Okay, I can try.

114
00:11:08,040 --> 00:11:09,120
Would you like to go in?

115
00:11:19,400 --> 00:11:20,400
No? Okay.

116
00:11:22,520 --> 00:11:23,680
This is for you.

117
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:27,160
It looks so good. Thank you.

118
00:11:27,240 --> 00:11:29,280
That's all right.
Can I have a napkin?

119
00:11:30,360 --> 00:11:31,360
Can I have a bite?

120
00:11:35,360 --> 00:11:36,480
So good. Here.

121
00:11:48,560 --> 00:11:49,640
Oh, that's very good.

122
00:12:01,720 --> 00:12:02,720
Come on.

123
00:12:13,680 --> 00:12:14,680
Okay.

124
00:12:30,600 --> 00:12:32,000
- Sit.
- Oh, no.

125
00:12:35,040 --> 00:12:36,600
Get up. What are you doing?

126
00:12:36,680 --> 00:12:37,840
- Are you okay?
- I fell back.

127
00:12:42,400 --> 00:12:43,400
It's fine.

128
00:13:53,920 --> 00:13:56,640
Father, I would like to introduce you
to Patrizia Reggiani.

129
00:13:56,720 --> 00:13:58,640
Patrizia, this is my father, Rodolfo.

130
00:13:58,720 --> 00:14:00,720
Delighted to meet you.

131
00:14:02,040 --> 00:14:05,200
I trust Adele has been
keeping you amused.

132
00:14:06,080 --> 00:14:07,120
Picasso?

133
00:14:07,720 --> 00:14:10,120
No... no. It's Klimt.

134
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:14,120
How silly of me.

135
00:14:14,200 --> 00:14:15,920
Oh, no... no.

136
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:18,520
It's an easy mistake.
I've made worse myself.

137
00:14:18,840 --> 00:14:20,680
Must be worth a fortune.

138
00:14:23,400 --> 00:14:28,760
Yes. But you know, to me,
art, like beauty, has no price.

139
00:14:29,360 --> 00:14:31,320
I made a reservation
for us at the Gallia.

140
00:14:31,480 --> 00:14:32,520
Perfect choice.

141
00:14:39,040 --> 00:14:40,160
So Patrizia...

142
00:14:40,520 --> 00:14:41,520
What...

143
00:14:42,720 --> 00:14:44,640
What exactly are your interests?

144
00:14:45,920 --> 00:14:48,160
I'm a very social person.

145
00:14:48,240 --> 00:14:50,600
- Are you?
- A people pleaser.

146
00:14:53,600 --> 00:14:56,480
And do you study?

147
00:14:58,280 --> 00:15:00,480
I work for my father's business.

148
00:15:02,280 --> 00:15:04,200
And his business is?

149
00:15:07,640 --> 00:15:09,320
Ground transportation.

150
00:15:23,520 --> 00:15:26,320
Maurizio said
you used to be an actor.

151
00:15:27,400 --> 00:15:29,160
Yes, I was.

152
00:15:29,560 --> 00:15:32,680
You may remember a film,
<i>The Ancestor?</i>

153
00:15:35,960 --> 00:15:37,640
No... no. Of course.

154
00:15:37,720 --> 00:15:38,720
You're too young.

155
00:15:38,800 --> 00:15:42,520
But sometimes on the TV,
they play a movie <i>Tourist Train.</i>

156
00:15:42,600 --> 00:15:44,560
- <i>Tourist Train</i> sounds familiar.
- Yeah, well...

157
00:15:44,640 --> 00:15:49,520
Maybe you noticed a dashing
young actor, Maurizio D'Ancora.

158
00:15:51,280 --> 00:15:52,360
That would have been me.

159
00:15:53,640 --> 00:15:56,320
I didn't know I was sitting
with a movie star.

160
00:15:56,560 --> 00:15:57,600
Can I get an autograph?

161
00:15:57,680 --> 00:15:59,040
Oh, no... no.

162
00:15:59,120 --> 00:16:01,920
The only good thing
that came from my career was

163
00:16:02,480 --> 00:16:04,440
meeting Maurizio's mother.

164
00:16:04,840 --> 00:16:08,240
Now she, she was a star.

165
00:16:10,240 --> 00:16:12,080
I remember at her funeral

166
00:16:13,280 --> 00:16:18,320
during a moment of silent remembrance

167
00:16:18,920 --> 00:16:21,760
Maurizio noticed the priest
lighting candles

168
00:16:23,480 --> 00:16:24,880
and he began to sing

169
00:16:25,640 --> 00:16:26,920
<i>Happy Birthday.</i>

170
00:16:28,200 --> 00:16:32,880
He turned, maybe
the saddest moment of my life

171
00:16:33,680 --> 00:16:35,120
into something...

172
00:16:35,560 --> 00:16:37,400
How do you say, something sweet.

173
00:16:40,760 --> 00:16:41,880
That's my son.

174
00:16:43,720 --> 00:16:45,200
That is my dear boy.

175
00:17:07,600 --> 00:17:09,560
- <i>Grazie,</i> Franco.
- Thank you, sir.

176
00:17:31,240 --> 00:17:32,920
Ah, Maurizio.

177
00:17:33,960 --> 00:17:35,760
I liked your Patrizia.

178
00:17:36,720 --> 00:17:37,720
Charming.

179
00:17:38,120 --> 00:17:39,680
Father, she really liked you.

180
00:17:44,360 --> 00:17:46,200
Tell me, where did you meet her?

181
00:17:46,880 --> 00:17:48,600
I met her at a party.

182
00:17:49,200 --> 00:17:50,200
Party?

183
00:17:50,280 --> 00:17:52,960
Yeah, Luca Sarzana's house.
At the Palazzo Serbelloni.

184
00:17:53,040 --> 00:17:54,880
Yes, I know where the Sarzanas live.

185
00:17:59,120 --> 00:18:00,120
You know...

186
00:18:02,160 --> 00:18:04,720
there is a certain sort
of young woman

187
00:18:05,600 --> 00:18:09,800
who makes their fortune

188
00:18:09,880 --> 00:18:13,160
from getting their hooks
into someone like you.

189
00:18:13,240 --> 00:18:15,960
Well, yes, Father,
but... but Patrizia is not like that.

190
00:18:16,040 --> 00:18:20,360
Well, I had Franco
do a little investigation.

191
00:18:20,680 --> 00:18:23,960
I think she's after your money.
Like they all are.

192
00:18:24,280 --> 00:18:25,680
The Reggianis...

193
00:18:27,080 --> 00:18:28,800
are truck drivers.

194
00:18:28,880 --> 00:18:32,720
Her father has a very successful
transportation business.

195
00:18:32,800 --> 00:18:33,800
It is...

196
00:18:35,680 --> 00:18:36,960
It is an empire.

197
00:18:38,200 --> 00:18:40,600
A truck driving empire. How many?

198
00:18:41,160 --> 00:18:43,200
- How many what?
- How many trucks?

199
00:18:43,280 --> 00:18:45,040
50? 500?

200
00:18:45,120 --> 00:18:47,320
What does he transport, garbage? Huh?

201
00:18:47,400 --> 00:18:48,400
Mafia!

202
00:18:58,160 --> 00:19:00,400
Listen, I've...

203
00:19:01,080 --> 00:19:02,160
I give you everything.

204
00:19:02,240 --> 00:19:03,840
I give you this house,
I give you money.

205
00:19:03,920 --> 00:19:05,720
You have a life. You...

206
00:19:06,880 --> 00:19:08,200
What is it you want?

207
00:19:10,040 --> 00:19:11,920
What I want is to marry her.

208
00:19:13,200 --> 00:19:15,320
Live with her. Fuck her.
Have a good time with her.

209
00:19:15,400 --> 00:19:17,960
Do what you want.
Go away on holiday. Go to Sardinia.

210
00:19:18,040 --> 00:19:19,520
But no, not marry.

211
00:19:23,360 --> 00:19:24,840
No, don't walk away.

212
00:19:24,920 --> 00:19:25,920
Okay, listen to yourself.

213
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:28,280
You're so bitter
and you don't even realize it.

214
00:19:28,360 --> 00:19:31,840
Who cares what her family name is
or how many trucks they have.

215
00:19:32,920 --> 00:19:34,720
You hide here in the past

216
00:19:35,520 --> 00:19:37,480
and you expect me
to hide here with you?

217
00:19:38,560 --> 00:19:40,280
Not anymore!

218
00:19:41,840 --> 00:19:43,200
These are your ghosts.

219
00:19:45,360 --> 00:19:47,200
These are your ghosts, not mine.

220
00:19:47,280 --> 00:19:48,520
These are your regrets.

221
00:19:49,520 --> 00:19:50,920
Don't do this to me.

222
00:19:51,760 --> 00:19:53,360
You can't stop it.

223
00:19:53,440 --> 00:19:55,920
I can, I will.
I will... I cut you from my will.

224
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:57,280
I'll leave you with nothing.

225
00:19:58,440 --> 00:19:59,440
That's fine.

226
00:20:01,400 --> 00:20:02,400
I love her.

227
00:20:02,880 --> 00:20:04,960
You're making a big mistake.

228
00:20:05,680 --> 00:20:09,400
Oh, she's fine,
but, you know, she's a...

229
00:20:09,960 --> 00:20:11,160
She's just a...

230
00:20:11,240 --> 00:20:12,600
I love what she is.

231
00:20:29,360 --> 00:20:30,360
<i>Sí?</i>

232
00:20:30,480 --> 00:20:33,320
<i>Commendatory</i> Reggiani,
my name is Maurizio Gucci.

233
00:20:34,720 --> 00:20:35,880
Patrizia!

234
00:20:37,120 --> 00:20:38,120
(Italian)

235
00:20:38,800 --> 00:20:42,880
I have had a disagreement
with my father

236
00:20:42,960 --> 00:20:46,200
that has forced me to leave
my home and my family business.

237
00:20:46,840 --> 00:20:48,760
I am still in school.

238
00:20:49,040 --> 00:20:52,360
I'm studying to be a lawyer,
so as of this moment, I...

239
00:20:53,080 --> 00:20:55,240
I do not have a job, but I...

240
00:20:55,320 --> 00:20:56,320
(Italian)

241
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:00,720
But I'm in love with your daughter.

242
00:21:03,560 --> 00:21:05,000
And I would like to marry her.

243
00:21:05,280 --> 00:21:07,600
Although, now I have
nothing to offer her.

244
00:21:08,240 --> 00:21:10,480
I... I need a job.

245
00:21:14,480 --> 00:21:15,480
Mom.

246
00:21:20,520 --> 00:21:21,560
Mama.

247
00:22:13,480 --> 00:22:17,520
Maurizio Gucci,
you're urgently needed in accounting.

248
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:21,720
Maurizio... Maurizio!

249
00:22:42,040 --> 00:22:43,040
That was great.

250
00:22:44,280 --> 00:22:46,400
The door! The door!

251
00:23:01,400 --> 00:23:02,400
Papa?

252
00:23:07,000 --> 00:23:08,000
Papa?

253
00:24:58,880 --> 00:25:00,480
Hi, Papa.

254
00:25:03,680 --> 00:25:04,760
(Italian)

255
00:25:23,880 --> 00:25:25,760
<i>Ciao, ciao.</i>

256
00:25:45,200 --> 00:25:46,520
(Italian)

257
00:25:47,880 --> 00:25:49,480
(Italian)

258
00:25:51,080 --> 00:25:52,080
(Italian)

259
00:25:53,880 --> 00:26:01,640
(Italian)

260
00:26:14,080 --> 00:26:15,280
Maurizio...

261
00:26:17,520 --> 00:26:24,000
I'll love you forever,
for the rest of my life.

262
00:26:26,080 --> 00:26:27,160
Me too.

263
00:26:28,000 --> 00:26:31,120
(Italian)

264
00:27:26,160 --> 00:27:27,560
What is this?

265
00:27:31,000 --> 00:27:32,320
Where is this?

266
00:27:32,600 --> 00:27:33,640
What is this?

267
00:27:38,720 --> 00:27:40,720
What is this?

268
00:27:42,440 --> 00:27:43,560
How about that.

269
00:27:54,760 --> 00:27:55,760
Yes.

270
00:27:56,920 --> 00:27:58,440
Ah, Claudia.

271
00:27:58,520 --> 00:27:59,576
- <i>Buona sera.</i>
- Good morning!

272
00:27:59,600 --> 00:28:00,880
Good morning, Mr. Aldo.

273
00:28:00,960 --> 00:28:01,960
Good morning.

