02:10:57,920 --> 02:11:00,680
"It took a German designer
to stir up Chanel"

1845
02:11:01,400 --> 02:11:04,000
and it is an American
who has put Gucci far and away

1846
02:11:04,120 --> 02:11:05,560
"in the front of fashion."

1847
02:11:09,160 --> 02:11:12,600
"Some say Mr. Ford will give
Mr. Lagerfeld a run for his money."

1848
02:11:18,480 --> 02:11:20,240
I have to call my mother in Austin.

1849
02:11:34,800 --> 02:11:36,760
Watch what you say, he's here.

1850
02:11:46,320 --> 02:11:48,200
What an unforgettable night.

1851
02:11:48,680 --> 02:11:49,680
Maurizio.

1852
02:11:51,000 --> 02:11:52,760
And the response is incredible.

1853
02:11:53,040 --> 02:11:54,880
I've never seen anything like it.

1854
02:11:55,280 --> 02:11:57,880
Indeed. It marks
a new chapter for Gucci.

1855
02:11:58,560 --> 02:12:01,760
Hey, try the carpaccio.
It melts in your mouth.

1856
02:12:01,840 --> 02:12:02,840
Okay.

1857
02:12:04,360 --> 02:12:06,960
Don't say anything
while I talk to him.

1858
02:12:07,040 --> 02:12:08,920
- (Arabic)
- I'll call on you when you can talk.

1859
02:12:12,400 --> 02:12:14,656
I think we can all be honest with
each other around this table, yeah?

1860
02:12:14,680 --> 02:12:15,800
We're all friends here.

1861
02:12:16,400 --> 02:12:18,200
We can... we all respect each other.

1862
02:12:19,280 --> 02:12:20,280
<i>Grazie.</i>

1863
02:12:23,400 --> 02:12:24,440
We're very concerned.

1864
02:12:26,680 --> 02:12:28,000
What concerns you?

1865
02:12:28,760 --> 02:12:29,760
Numbers.

1866
02:12:30,640 --> 02:12:32,160
Specifically, Gucci's.

1867
02:12:34,200 --> 02:12:36,240
Well, you said you didn't care
about numbers.

1868
02:12:36,320 --> 02:12:38,200
That you trusted your instinct.

1869
02:12:38,760 --> 02:12:41,680
Yeah. I care about numbers
when they're terrible numbers.

1870
02:12:44,080 --> 02:12:47,400
Our projections for 1996 are abysmal.

1871
02:12:48,240 --> 02:12:50,120
By slashing hundreds
of profitable items...

1872
02:12:50,200 --> 02:12:52,320
You mean my uncle's knickknacks?

1873
02:12:55,760 --> 02:12:59,560
Losses are likely to
total $30 million this year on sales

1874
02:13:00,000 --> 02:13:01,720
of $180 million.

1875
02:13:01,800 --> 02:13:05,000
Down from $210 million in 1991.

1876
02:13:06,200 --> 02:13:08,560
And $270 million.

1877
02:13:09,200 --> 02:13:11,680
There is $85 million in bank debts.

1878
02:13:12,480 --> 02:13:14,360
We may even have trouble

1879
02:13:14,440 --> 02:13:16,560
paying salaries
for the next couple of months.

1880
02:13:17,640 --> 02:13:20,400
Profits remain elusive.

1881
02:13:20,480 --> 02:13:21,480
And I've always said that

1882
02:13:21,560 --> 02:13:23,880
our strategic plan
would take five years.

1883
02:13:23,960 --> 02:13:27,440
It's not about immediate profit.
You go down to come back up again.

1884
02:13:27,520 --> 02:13:29,240
That is how you get out of a stall.

1885
02:13:29,640 --> 02:13:31,920
But the personal items
are a concern as well.

1886
02:13:33,000 --> 02:13:36,840
All paid for through Gucci's accounts
and charged as expenses.

1887
02:13:36,920 --> 02:13:39,400
The multimillion-dollar antiques
in the stores.

1888
02:13:39,480 --> 02:13:40,800
The purchase of countless cars

1889
02:13:40,880 --> 02:13:43,880
including a Ferrari F40
and a Lamborghini Countach.

1890
02:13:43,960 --> 02:13:47,080
$3 million on a watch,
a Patek Philippe 2523.

1891
02:13:47,160 --> 02:13:50,200
$7 million on a luxury penthouse.
I could go on and on.

1892
02:13:50,560 --> 02:13:53,080
An 18th century palatial villa
outside Florence

1893
02:13:53,160 --> 02:13:54,760
for use as a training center.

1894
02:13:54,840 --> 02:13:57,200
I have justifications
for all of these things

1895
02:13:57,320 --> 02:13:59,840
but it doesn't seem that
you're in a place to hear them.

1896
02:14:00,120 --> 02:14:03,880
Maurizio, please try and take this
in the spirit of our friendship.

1897
02:14:05,120 --> 02:14:06,520
We've been through a lot together.

1898
02:14:07,840 --> 02:14:09,520
You have many qualities.

1899
02:14:10,360 --> 02:14:11,840
But we must be realistic.

1900
02:14:11,920 --> 02:14:13,320
You're not a natural manager.

1901
02:14:13,880 --> 02:14:18,360
You can't run a business
purely on charm and eccentricities.

1902
02:14:18,440 --> 02:14:20,640
No. You need time as well.

1903
02:14:23,320 --> 02:14:25,200
Last night does mark
a new chapter for Gucci

1904
02:14:25,280 --> 02:14:26,776
and I am the one
that brought it to you.

1905
02:14:26,800 --> 02:14:29,320
Maurizio, I want you to understand

1906
02:14:29,400 --> 02:14:33,080
whatever happens between
both of our companies

1907
02:14:33,160 --> 02:14:37,880
I have never stopped
respecting you or your vision.

1908
02:14:39,400 --> 02:14:41,680
But I have vision for my people too.

1909
02:14:42,200 --> 02:14:43,840
And I have a business to run.

1910
02:14:50,520 --> 02:14:55,200
We want to offer you $150 million
for your 50% stake in Gucci.

1911
02:14:55,920 --> 02:14:57,160
You want to buy me out.

1912
02:14:57,560 --> 02:14:59,200
We want to save the business.

1913
02:15:00,080 --> 02:15:02,240
And who would be appointed CEO?

1914
02:15:13,360 --> 02:15:15,040
She was right about you.

1915
02:15:19,320 --> 02:15:21,360
$150 million.

1916
02:15:21,760 --> 02:15:22,800
You'll be a rich man.

1917
02:15:22,880 --> 02:15:24,400
If you really think it's about money

1918
02:15:24,480 --> 02:15:26,920
then you know less about Gucci
than I thought.

1919
02:15:29,000 --> 02:15:30,640
Hurry up and eat, boys.

1920
02:15:43,360 --> 02:15:47,200
I've never tasted
such good meat in my life.

1921
02:15:49,680 --> 02:15:50,720
- Excuse me.
- Yes.

1922
02:15:50,800 --> 02:15:53,000
This meat. Where is it coming from?

1923
02:15:53,280 --> 02:15:55,120
This is the finest beef in Tuscany.

1924
02:15:55,440 --> 02:15:57,040
It comes from the Val di Chiana.

1925
02:15:57,320 --> 02:15:59,040
The cows are treated like royalty.

1926
02:19:22,360 --> 02:19:23,400
That's him.

1927
02:19:23,600 --> 02:19:25,200
- Good morning.
- <i>Ciao.</i>

1928
02:19:38,120 --> 02:19:39,280
<i>Signor</i> Gucci?

1929
02:19:57,360 --> 02:19:58,480
What's going on?

1930
02:22:12,600 --> 02:22:13,600
Patrizia.

1931
02:22:23,320 --> 02:22:24,320
I know.

1932
02:22:33,360 --> 02:22:36,400
Please see <i>Signorina</i> Franchi
out of my house.

1933
02:23:35,840 --> 02:23:36,920
<i>Signora</i> Reggiani.

1934
02:23:41,160 --> 02:23:42,360
<i>Signora</i> Reggiani.

1935
02:23:46,680 --> 02:23:47,960
<i>Signora</i> Reggiani.

1936
02:23:55,320 --> 02:23:58,800
You can call me <i>Signora</i> Gucci.
